  ---
  Code Review: KD-Collaboration Pitch Deck App

  Overall Assessment

  Strengths:
  - Clean, simple architecture appropriate for a pitch deck
  - Good use of Next.js 15 App Router with Server Components
  - Nice custom color palette and typography choices
  - Separation of content (JSON) from presentation (components)
  - Responsive design with Tailwind CSS
  - Print-friendly styling

  Concerns & Areas for Improvement:
  Multiple architectural, accessibility, performance, and user experience issues that could be significantly
   enhanced.

  ---
  What I Would Have Done Differently

  1. CRITICAL: NavBar Functionality is Broken

  Location: components/NavBar.tsx:5-28

  Problem: The navigation bar maintains state (idx) but doesn't actually navigate anywhere. Clicking
  "Next/Prev" updates local state but the slides remain visible all at once. This is a fundamental UX
  failure.

  What I'd do:
  - Either implement proper slide-by-slide navigation with scroll behavior
  - Or remove the non-functional navigation entirely
  - Consider using hash-based navigation (#slide-1, #slide-2) or React state that hides/shows slides

  2. Component Architecture & Reusability

  Current Issues:
  - Components are too specific (e.g., TableSlide, MetricsLoop) - hard to extend
  - No shared layout/spacing patterns
  - Hardcoded styling scattered everywhere
  - Missing component composition patterns

  What I'd do:
  // Create base components with better composition
  <Card variant="slide" size="lg">
    <Card.Header>
      <Heading level={2}>{title}</Heading>
    </Card.Header>
    <Card.Body>{content}</Card.Body>
  </Card>

  3. Accessibility Issues

  Critical Problems:
  - Missing semantic HTML throughout
  - No ARIA labels on interactive elements
  - No focus management
  - Poor keyboard navigation
  - No skip links
  - Color contrast may be insufficient (plum #812D6B on cream #FAF8F3)

  Location Examples:
  - components/NavBar.tsx:10-24 - Button states not announced
  - components/TitleCard.tsx:16 - Image alt text is generic
  - app/page.tsx:16-64 - No landmark roles or skip navigation

  What I'd do:
  // Add proper semantic structure
  <nav aria-label="Slide navigation">
    <button 
      aria-label={`Previous slide, currently on ${idx + 1} of ${total}`}
      aria-disabled={idx === 0}
    >

  4. Performance & Image Optimization

  Issues:
  - No image dimensions specified (causes layout shift)
  - Missing image optimization strategy
  - No lazy loading for below-fold content
  - Fonts not optimized with next/font

  Location: components/TitleCard.tsx:15-17

  What I'd do:
  import { Playfair_Display, Inter } from 'next/font/google'

  const playfair = Playfair_Display({ subsets: ['latin'], variable: '--font-display' })

  // In Image component:
  <Image
    src={image}
    alt="Kamala Devi presenting at workshop"
    fill
    sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 40vw"
    priority={true} // for above-fold images
    className="object-cover"
  />

  5. Type Safety Issues

  Problems:
  - Inline type definitions instead of shared types
  - any types implicit in some places
  - No validation for JSON content
  - Props spread without proper typing

  Location: app/page.tsx:49 - inline type (b: string, i: number)

  What I'd do:
  // types/slides.ts
  export interface SlideContent {
    title: TitleSlide;
    alignment: TextSlide;
    help: TableSlide;
    // ... with proper validation
  }

  // Add runtime validation
  import { z } from 'zod'
  const SlideSchema = z.object({...})

  6. Content Management Strategy

  Current Issues:
  - All content in one massive slides.json file
  - No content validation
  - Hard to maintain/edit for non-technical users
  - No CMS integration path

  What I'd do:
  - Split into separate JSON files per slide
  - Add a simple CMS (Sanity, Contentful, or even Markdown + frontmatter)
  - Implement Zod schemas for validation
  - Create a content editing interface

  7. Styling & Design System

  Issues:
  - Magic numbers everywhere (px-6, py-10, text-4xl)
  - Inconsistent spacing patterns
  - No design tokens beyond colors
  - Tailwind config underutilized
  - Custom fonts not loaded via next/font (performance issue)

  Locations: Throughout all components

  What I'd do:
  // tailwind.config.ts - add design tokens
  theme: {
    extend: {
      spacing: {
        'slide-padding': '2.5rem',
        'card-gap': '1.5rem',
      },
      fontSize: {
        'slide-title': ['2.5rem', { lineHeight: '1.2' }],
      },
    }
  }

  8. Error Handling & Loading States

  Missing:
  - No error boundaries
  - No loading states for async content
  - No fallbacks for missing images/data
  - No 404 handling

  Location: app/appendix/page.tsx:8-26

  What I'd do:
  export default async function AppendixPage() {
    try {
      const [profile, trial] = await Promise.all([
        loadMdx("appendix/profile.mdx"),
        loadMdx("appendix/trial-sprint.mdx")
      ])
    } catch (error) {
      return <ErrorDisplay error={error} />
    }
    // ... render
  }

  9. SEO & Metadata

  Issues:
  - Basic metadata only
  - No Open Graph tags
  - No Twitter cards
  - No structured data (JSON-LD)
  - Missing canonical URLs
  - No sitemap

  Location: app/layout.tsx:4-7

  What I'd do:
  export const metadata: Metadata = {
    title: "Creating Spaciousness Through Structure â€” David Kellam",
    description: "Operations support for creative professionals...",
    openGraph: {
      title: "...",
      description: "...",
      images: ['/og-image.jpg'],
      type: 'website',
    },
    twitter: {
      card: 'summary_large_image',
    },
    // Add JSON-LD structured data
  }

  10. Animation & Interactions

  Current:
  - Framer Motion installed but completely unused
  - No transitions between states
  - Static, lifeless presentation

  What I'd do:
  // Add subtle, purposeful animations
  import { motion } from 'framer-motion'

  <motion.section
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
    whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    viewport={{ once: true }}
  >
    {slideContent}
  </motion.section>

  11. Code Organization

  Issues:
  - No lib/ utilities folder structure
  - Types scattered inline
  - No constants file
  - No hooks directory
  - mdx.ts in wrong location (should be in utilities)

  What I'd do:
  /app
  /components
    /ui (base components)
    /slides (slide-specific)
  /lib
    /utils
    /hooks
    /constants
  /types
  /content

  12. Testing & Documentation

  Missing:
  - Zero tests
  - No component documentation
  - No README with setup instructions
  - No prop documentation

  What I'd do:
  - Add Vitest + React Testing Library
  - Document components with TSDoc
  - Create comprehensive README
  - Add Storybook for component development

